<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[175,1005,1390,1570]" lastBlockId="5.[148,977,1000,1100]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,1443,1464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body black. Rostrum longer than head but shorter than prothorax. Antennae inserted slightly in front of middle of the rostrum, funicle 7-segmented, longer than club, its 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[382,394,1491,1505]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">st</superScript>
flagellar segment longer and broader than others, nearly as long as the next two segments combined. Prothorax with obtuse teeth near middle of the lateral margins, median carina distinct. Scutellum flat, not completely filling space between elytral bases and pronotum. Elytral striae narrower, with regular punctures; intervals flat, rugose, 2–3 times broader than striae. All femora stout and with teeth, that of profemur larger. Inner margin of tibiae minutely serrulated. Claws simple, without basal teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
